GateDocument.TextWithNodes: Workshop on Query Processing for Semistructured Data and Non- Standard Data Formats Wednesday , January 13 , 1999 Jerusalem , Israel In conjunction with ICDT'99 CALL FOR PAPERS and ATTENDANCE - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - We have witnessed a considerable interest recently in managing data that does not conform to a conventional relational or object-oriented schema : the term "semistructured" has been used with this unconventional kind of data . This interest is motivated by a variety of applications , such as the integration of heterogeneous data sources , querying the WWW , managing web sites , or new database applications such as biology databases . The recently approved Web data exchange standard , XML , will soon allow applications to exchange data freely on the web . Most of the research so far has focused on the modeling and querying of semistructured data , addressing issues such as designing data models and query languages , extracting structure from semi-structured data and the analysis of the expressive power of query languages . The purpose of this workshop is to bring together researchers interested in efficiency issues related to semistructured data and other non-standard data formats , like XML . The topics of interest include , but are not limited to : efficient storage and indexing , query optimization , updates specification , incremental updates , statistics gathering , etc . The workshop will be rather informal and will encourage discussion and interaction . We invite submissions of short papers ( 5 pages or less ) . An informal proceedings will be published . A summary of the workshop , the accepted papers , a summary of the panel 's discussions , and the list of participants will be made available on the Web . There will be a registration fee of $ 50 . PAPER SUBMISSIONS : Please send a postscript file by e-mail to Daniela . Florescu @ yvt . kl . yy . The deadline for submissions is Oct . 31 , 1998 . If you would like to attend , but will not be submitting a paper , please send email indicating your interest in attending , by Dec . 7 , 1998 .
